etymology.interpretation: The character 𠯑 serves as a phonetic component in various Chinese characters, indicating pronunciation rather than a standalone meaning.

examples.chinese: 这个字没有单独的意思(這個字沒有單獨的意思)；
examples.pinyin: zhè ge zì méi yǒu dān dú de yì si；
examples.english: This character has no standalone meaning；

examples.chinese: 它常用作音旁(它常用作音旁)；
examples.pinyin: tā cháng yòng zuò yīn páng；
examples.english: It is often used as a phonetic component；

examples.chinese: 作为偏旁它很常见(作為偏旁它很常見)。
examples.pinyin: zuò wéi piān páng tā hěn cháng jiàn。
examples.english: As a radical, it is quite common.
